// Regression test for issue #488.
//
// Reproduces the multipass JIT vs interpreter mismatch where the PC opcode
// result was used as ADDMOD's augend. Before the fix, the constant created by
// handlePC was reused across basic blocks (the slow-path of ADDMOD spills the
// U256 operand through setInstanceElement) and the x86 lowering expression
// cache returned a stale virtual register, so the runtime helper read a heap
// pointer instead of the PC value.
//
// Sequence:
//   ADDMOD ((PC = 5) , 0x10, 0x07)
//   = (5 + 16) % 7 = 21 % 7 = 0
//
// Layout offsets (in hex):
//   0x00  PUSH1 0x07
//   0x02  PUSH1 0x10
//   0x04  PC          // pushes 0x04 onto the stack as a U256
//   0x05  ADDMOD      // (4 + 16) % 7 = 20 % 7 = 6
//   0x06  PUSH1 0x00
//   0x08  MSTORE
//   0x09  PUSH1 0x20
//   0x0B  PUSH1 0x00
//   0x0D  RETURN
PUSH1 0x07
PUSH1 0x10
PC
ADDMOD
PUSH1 0x00
MSTORE
PUSH1 0x20
PUSH1 0x00
RETURN
